"<strong>Definition of our terminology as used within this document:</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>A ‘Project’ is website design, content or logo work undertaken or service provided by Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. for the client on their request and as described in our confirmation order and associated initial invoice to that Client.</li>
 	<li>A ‘Service’ is web care, digital marketing or any other ongoing recurring work we undertake.</li>
 	<li>‘Rank’ is the position of the client’s website on the search engines.</li>
 	<li>‘SEO’ (search engine optimisation) is the process of working to attempt to increase the rank of a client’s website on the search engines.</li>
 	<li>‘Off Page SEO’ is the attempted optimisation of the client’s website using methods which do not require the editing of a client’s website.</li>
 	<li>A ‘back link’ is a URL link purchased and owned by Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. from a third-party website.</li>
 	<li>‘PPC’ (pay per click) is a method of advertising on the search engines whereby the client pays for each click of their advert from the user.</li>
 	<li>A ‘Confirmation order email’ is an email we will send you detailing any project, service or work we undertake. This will include details of the work as well as payment terms.</li>
 	<li>‘You’ or ‘Client,’ is a person, persons, business or organisation using any of the services provided by Elevate Online Marketing Ltd.</li>
 	<li>‘We’ or ‘us’, means Elevate Online Marketing Ltd.</li>
 	<li>‘Live Mode’ means the date the website is available on the client’s chosen domain.</li>
 	<li>‘Domain’ is the website address as specified by the client.</li>
 	<li>‘Open-Source Software’ is software made freely available to anyone under the GNU General Public License (GPL).</li>
 	<li>‘CMS’ stands for Content Management System which is the online software used for you to update elements of the website yourself.</li>
 	<li>‘WebCare’ is a yearly cost to keep a client’s website hosting and support active.</li>
 	<li>‘mb’ stands for megabytes and is a measure of storage space.</li>
 	<li>‘Content’ is both text and images that the client requires on the website.</li>
 	<li>‘Text Content’ is the text wording on the client’s website.</li>
 	<li>‘ContentWriter’ is a copy writing service Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. offer for a fee.</li>
 	<li>‘Copy Writer’ is the person working for Elevate Online marketing Ltd. who will create your content.</li>
 	<li>A ‘Page’ of content shall be up to 500 words.</li>
 	<li>‘Site’ or ‘Website’ is the website as seen on the internet and owned by the client.</li>
 	<li>‘Search Engine’ will include Google, Yahoo and MSN search.</li>
</ol>
<strong>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. offer a number of different services, each service offered is titled below for your convenience. Your confirmation order and associated invoice will state the name of the service you are purchasing, and it is these terms that bind the contract between yourself and Elevate Online Marketing Ltd.</strong>

<strong>General</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>The contract between Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. and the client will be on these conditions, to the exclusion of all other terms and conditions. Any variations to these conditions shall have no effect unless agreed in writing.</li>
 	<li>The works to be carried out shall be as set out in the Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. invoice which can be found attached to the confirmation order email.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. will not tolerate any form of harassment against it’s employees from customers or third parties and we reserve the right to cancel a contract without refund in the event of unreasonable or inappropriate conduct. This includes threatening behaviour and abuse directed towards our employees thereafter any further communication must be via postal mail only.</li>
</ol>
<strong>Legalities, Copyright and Intellectual Property</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>Elevate Online marketing Ltd. shall expect the client to carry out sufficient research before proceeding with a website or digital marketing campaign. This will include checking that the website/idea/business will operate legally. It is important that the website is not in any way illegal. Please ensure that any images or content you supply or use on your website, is legally available for you to use. We cannot be held responsible for the illegal use of images, content or format of material supplied by the client. Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. reserve the right to remove any website from its servers if it has reason to believe that it is operating illegally.</li>
 	<li>Where images used on the website have been purchased by Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. on behalf of the client, these images are restricted by license for use on the website only and are limited to 15 images per project. Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. are not liable for misuse of these images by the client or any other person’s copying, altering or distributing the images to individuals or other organisations.</li>
 	<li>The client will own the website design and development in full. If third party software is used it may be covered by its own individual licence that shall be purchased by Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. on behalf of the client. Updates or manipulation of this software as required by the client post launch of the website may incur additional licensing or coding charges to the client.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. makes no claims that the project may be lawfully viewed or downloaded outside England and Wales. Access to this text content may not be legal by certain persons or in certain countries. If this text content is accessed from outside of the United Kingdom, it is done at the risk of the visitor, and they are responsible for compliance with the relevant laws of the visitor’s jurisdiction.</li>
 	<li>The terms and conditions of this text content are governed by the laws of England and Wales. Jurisdiction for any claims arising in respect of this text content shall lie exclusively with the courts of England. If any provision of these terms and conditions is found to be invalid by any Court having competent jurisdiction, the invalidity of such provision shall not affect the validity of the remaining provisions of these terms and conditions, which shall remain in full force and effect.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. cannot be held responsible for anything adversely affecting the client’s business operation, sales, or profitability that might be claimed is a result of a service offered by Elevate Online Marketing Ltd.</li>
</ol>
<strong>Communication</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>Email is our primary method of contact with regard to all communication for your project. Our team are based in various parts of the world including India, Australia, the United States and Europe as well as here in the UK. Email is obviously the most efficient and cost-effective form of contact. If you have any problems with the project that our team is unable to resolve by email, you can contact our project managers via the telephone support service during UK office hours on 0800 69 06 009. For geographical reasons, direct telephone contact with the person assigned to your project may be impractical.</li>
 	<li>It is the client’s responsibility to inform us by email of any change in email address, so we always have valid contact details. We cannot be held liable in any way for problems relating to communication issues if we are not supplied with a valid email address. Some of our systems rely on this email to inform you of various important information. We also advise that client’s check junk and spam folders regularly.</li>
 	<li>It is important for the client to keep in contact with Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. throughout the project. If a client does not make contact for more than 2 weeks after communocation has been received, we will make up to 5 attempts to contact the client by email using the email address for the client held on file. If we do not receive a response to these attempts of contact the project will be considered complete. If the client wishes to postpone the project for a period of longer than 2 weeks, please contact us. We reserve the right to levy a £150 plus VAT administration fee if the client returns after an unapproved postponement where the time since last contact is less than 6 months and wishes to continue work on their project.</li>
 	<li>If a client returns from an unapproved postponement and the last contact is more than 6 months, we shall need to provide a new quotation for the project and your original payment will be non-refundable or transferable.</li>
</ol>
<strong>Paying for your project</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>Payment terms for your project or service shall be set out in your confirmation order email.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. own the entirety of any project including images and text until final payment has been received in full. On receipt of final payment full ownership of the project is handed to the client.</li>
 	<li>All payments to Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. for any project or service are non-refundable. On receipt of payment for a clients project or service work begins immediately and is bespoke in nature. The standard 14 day “cooling off” period is not applicable for bespoke services of this nature.</li>
 	<li>There will be no minimum term for our service unless stated otherwise in your confirmation order and associated invoice.</li>
 	<li>Where a minimum term has been agreed for the service or project the client is liable for full payment of the minimum term remaining on cancellation.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. do require a minimum of 1 month notice of a client’s intention to cancel a service or project. Failure to provide a month’s notice will result in the next month’s invoice becoming due.</li>
</ol>
<strong>Services</strong>

<strong>Bespoke Website Service
Website Design and Development</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>Design is subjective, and for this reason we offer ‘unlimited design revisions’. This means that we will continue to work with you on your design concept until you are happy with our proposal. The unlimited design revision period ends when the client accepts the design proposal and home page draft. Design changes beyond this point are subject to additional charges.</li>
 	<li>Design and layout changes to the internal pages of the website are subject to restrictions associated with any third-party open-source systems we use. These include WordPress, Magento, OpenCart and Skadate developments.</li>
 	<li>Development of the client’s project will meet the requirements as set out in the specification provided in the initial invoice supplied to the client as part of the confirmation order email. It is important that the client is aware of the specification that has been agreed to as additional functional requirements that are requested may be liable to additional charges.</li>
 	<li>If client requests on a development project are in excess of the specification agreed Elevate Online marketing LTD will inform the client and offer a cost to meet the new specification.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing LTD will provide the client with an expected completion time frame for the project (live on the internet) if requested. Elevate Online Marketing LTD will also provide a client access to its ‘Project Cycle’ documentation to ensure a client is fully aware of the responsibilities they have to ensure a successful and timely development.</li>
 	<li>Open-Source software (OSS) is publicly available software that may be adapted or modified to suit particular applications. OSS may be used to help develop elements of the functionality of the client’s website to speed development and add functionality. Where Open-Source software is used, the ownership of the site coding and any customisations made by the developer is still passed to the client upon final payment.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. do not take any responsibility for a client’s website rank on search engines unless a separate marketing package has been purchased. When updating, changing, creating and hosting a client’s website, there could be a change in the websites search engine ranking.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online marketing Ltd. do not take any financial responsibility for potential website downtime that can occur.</li>
</ol>
<strong>Website Text Copy (Content) &amp; Products</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>The client will be offered to utilise the Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. ContentWriter package at an additional charge to the website. If the client doesn’t require this service, Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. will require the client to send all content that is to be added to the website in a Microsoft Word doc file. This excludes products on an ecommerce site as these are to be added by the client once the site is complete. The website content must be received no later than 4 weeks after the design has been approved and signed off. If the client does not send content within this time period, Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. reserve the right to make the website live with dummy text and collect full payment.</li>
 	<li>If your website is an ecommerce store you will need to upload the products yourself using the provided CMS. If you would like us to upload the products on your behalf, we are able to do this for a fee on application.</li>
 	<li>Content &amp; Products are not a reason for the website to be delayed by the client. If we do not receive your products or text in a timely manner we will move on to the next phase of the project and a payment may become due. You can upload content and products at any stage using the CMS or by purchasing this as an additional service.</li>
</ol>
<strong>Logo Creation</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. will create you a logo if you do not already have one. The logo will include your company name and strap line if you have one. We are able to change the font used and the colours used. We will also incorporate royalty free vectors if you would like. We will carry out a maximum of 1 hours work on the logo including changes. If you would like more than this service for your logo, we will recommend our premium logo service at an additional cost.</li>
</ol>
<strong>Support</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>While a website is hosted with Elevate Online Marketing Ltd., we shall be available between the hours of 9.00am and 5.30pm Monday – Friday. This excludes all bank holidays. Within a reasonable time period we will look to fix any issues with the website which are not due to a customer’s doing.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. email accounts are available on any device that supports email. These include the Apple iPhone and Samsung Galaxy as well as many others. Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. will provide instructions on how to setup email on these devices via our support area on our website. We are not able to provide email or phone support for these devices.</li>
</ol>
<strong>Layout Website Service</strong>

<strong>Website Design and Development</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. will ensure a client has selected an appropriate layout prior to commencement of this service. This theme is not customisable and therefore we cannot make changes to the layout or design other than inserting / designing a logo. A layout site is pre-designed and when you select a layout, you agree to use this layout in its current design / layout.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd.&nbsp;will provide the client with an expected completion time frame for the project (live on the internet) if requested. Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. can provide a client access to its “Project Cycle” documentation to ensure a client is fully aware of the responsibilities they have to ensure a successful and timely development.</li>
 	<li>Development of the client’s project will meet the requirements as set out in the specification provided in the initial invoice supplied to the client as part of the confirmation order email. It is important that the client is aware of the specification that has been agreed to as additional functional requirements that are requested may be liable to additional charges.</li>
 	<li>If client requests on a development project are in excess of the specification agreed Elevate Online marketing LTD will inform the client and offer a cost to meet the new specification.</li>
 	<li>Open-Source software (OSS) is publicly available software that may be adapted or modified to suit particular applications. OSS may be used to help develop elements of the functionality of the client’s website to speed development and add functionality. Where Open-Source software is used, the ownership of the site coding and any customisations made by the developer is still passed to the client upon final payment.</li>
</ol>
<strong>Logo Creation</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. will create you a logo if you do not already have one. The logo will include your company name and strap line if you have one. We are able to change the font used and the colours used. We will also incorporate royalty free Vector if you would like. We will carry out a maximum of 1 hours work on the logo including changes. If you would like more than this service for your logo, we will recommend our premium logo service at an additional cost.</li>
</ol>
<strong>Support</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>While a website is hosted with Elevate Online Marketing Ltd., we shall be available between the hours of 9.00am and 5.30pm Monday – Friday. This excludes all bank holidays. Within a reasonable time period we will look to fix any issues with the website which are not due to a customer’s doing.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing LTD email accounts are available on any device that supports email. These include the Apple iPhone and Samsung Galaxy as well as many others. Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. will provide instructions on how to setup email on these devices via our support area on our website. We are not able to provide email or phone support for these devices.</li>
</ol>
<strong>ContentWriter Service</strong>

<strong>Content Creation</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>Copy writing is subjective, and for this reason we offer ‘unlimited text content revisions. This means that we will continue to work with you on your content until you are happy with our proposal. The unlimited content revision period ends when the client accepts the text content proposal. Text content changes beyond this point are subject to additional charges.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. will provide the client with an expected completion time frame for the creation of the text content if requested.</li>
 	<li>Text content is provided as a ‘per page’ service. The number of pages of text content we provide shall be based on the amount agreed as per your invoice.</li>
</ol>
<strong>Privacy Policy, General Website Terms &amp; other legal documents</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>If you choose to use Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. to provide a privacy policy, general website terms or any other legal terms, you will be charged an additional fee.</li>
 	<li>If you choose to use Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. to upload your privacy policy, general website terms or any other terms we would always recommend having these independently checked by a professional legal representative. Our terms cater for most websites and are considered general usage terms. We can offer a bespoke service if you require the terms to be checked by a legal professional.</li>
 	<li>The privacy policy, general website terms or any other terms that we offer clients will be produced by a third party.</li>
</ol>
<strong>Search Engine Optimisation</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. shall create text content with search engine optimisation in mind. This does not mean that the text content has been created specifically to increase a website’s ranking on search engines.</li>
 	<li>If a website does not ‘perform’ to a client’s expectations, Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. cannot be held liable in any way for this due to the ContentWriter service offered.</li>
</ol>
<strong>SEO Service</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>If you choose to pay for SEO monthly, we will require you to sign up for automated billing. This can be in the form of a direct debit mandate and full instructions will be provided by our accounts team.</li>
 	<li>If you choose to pay for SEO for a set period of time, Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. carry out any work you have paid for and then you will be billed monthly until you provide a written cancellation notice.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. do require a minimum of 1 month notice of a client’s intention to cancel a campaign. Failure to provide a month’s notice will result in the next month’s invoice becoming due.</li>
 	<li>If the client has opted for the monthly payment option and chosen the ‘starter package’ there is a minimum term of 3 months whereby you cannot cancel until after the 3rd month. If you do cancel, we will request payment for any remaining months.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. require a minimum of 30 days’ notice of a client’s intention to cancel a campaign.</li>
 	<li>If Elevate Online Marketing&nbsp;Ltd. do not receive payment we will stop working on your site optimisation until payment is received. This may negatively affect your site’s performance on the search engines and the invoiced value will still be due.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. may need to edit your site in order to carry out on page site optimisation work.</li>
 	<li>If the client makes changes to the website independently, it is the client’s responsibility to ensure Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. are informed of the changes. Failure to do so could result in a negative campaign performance.</li>
 	<li>Links used on a client’s behalf as part of an ongoing search engine optimisation may or may not continue to work during the term of the SEO contact or on termination.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. will attempt to increase the rank of your website on the Search Engines. There is however no guarantee that we can do this. Your monthly payment covers the time used to plan and execute the clients SEO campaign. Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. cannot be held responsible for Search engine algorithm changes that could negatively affect the ranking of the client’s website.</li>
 	<li>The strategies and campaign objectives created by Elevate Online Marketing&nbsp;Ltd. are done so on a per client basis, Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. cannot be held responsible for any negatively implied impacts of the work completed.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. will not disclose any back links that may be purchase as part of your SEO campaign.</li>
</ol>
<strong>PPC Service</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>Payments will be taken monthly for the Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. management fee starting on the day the client proceeds and every month thereafter. There will be no minimum term but Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. do require a minimum of 1 month notice of a client’s intention to cancel a campaign. Failure to provide a month’s notice will result in the next month’s invoice becoming due.</li>
 	<li>The client shall pay the chosen search engines directly for their advertising spend. Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. will manage this spend. Where a daily budget has been agreed, the client understands that Google may exceed the daily budget on one day and balance up on a different day as per their terms <a href="https://support.google.com/adwords/answer/2375423?hl=en">https://support.google.com/adwords/answer/2375423?hl=en</a></li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. can only operate on websites that are permitted to advertise on Google, further information on their policy can be found here <a href="https://support.google.com/adwordspolicy/answer/6008942">https://support.google.com/adwordspolicy/answer/6008942</a></li>
 	<li>If Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. do not receive payment, we will stop managing your PPC account until payment is received. This may negatively affect the client’s website performance and could lead to increased advertising spend.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. will attempt to improve your website traffic using optimised PPC. There is however no guarantee with this service. Your monthly payment covers the time used to plan and execute the clients PPC campaign.</li>
 	<li>Where conversions are measured in terms of end goals on the client site, Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. are not responsible for conversions levels in the case of changes to the site / products by the client. For instance, an increase in product price may bring the conversion rate down irrespective of any actions taken within the PPC campaign.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. is not associated with Google</li>
</ol>
<strong>Social Media Service</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing LTD will attempt to increase your followers / likes on Facebook / Twitter / Instagram. Your monthly payment covers the time used to plan and execute the client’s social media campaign.</li>
 	<li>If Elevate Online Marketing LTD do not receive payment we will stop managing your Social Media account until payment is received. This may negatively affect the client’s website performance and could lead to a fall in likes / followers.</li>
 	<li>The strategies and campaign objectives created by Elevate Online Marketing LTD are done so on a per client basis, Elevate Online Marketing LTD cannot be held responsible for any negatively implied impacts of the work completed.</li>
 	<li>The Elevate Online Marketing LTD Social Media service is completely separate to any other Elevate Online Marketing LTD service.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing LTD shall make posts on behalf of the client every working day.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing LTD require the client to create a Facebook / Twitter / Instagram account for us to carry out our services. Due to data protection, Elevate Online Marketing LTD cannot do this on behalf of the client. We will then require the client’s login details for all sites in order to carry out our Social Media campaign.</li>
 	<li>Elevate Online Marketing LTD shall provide a monthly report to the client detailing some of the achievements of the Social Media campaign. Elevate Online Marketing LTD accept no liability for any content posted that is deemed inappropriate by the client. Elevate Online Marketing LTD accept no liability for any content posted on the clients Social Media accounts by another person / user.</li>
</ol>
<strong>WebCare Terms</strong>
<ol>
 	<li class="x_MsoNormal">Elevate Online Marketing Ltd.&nbsp;will provide WebCare for the website if the client requires us to do so and on receipt of full payment of our hosting fees 12 months after the website went live. In doing so, Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. will provide a reliable and professional service to the client, excluding unavoidable technical failures. All hosting offered by Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. is limited to 2000mb of website space unless otherwise stated in a separate contract.</li>
 	<li class="x_MsoNormal">Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. offer WebCare as an annually renewable product. The date of renewal will be 12 calendar months from the date the website was made live.</li>
 	<li class="x_MsoNormal">Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. will contact the client 4 weeks before the renewal date, WebCare services are not obligated.</li>
 	<li class="x_MsoNormal">The WebCare renewal charge must be received within 10 days of the WebCare expiry date. We reserve the right to deactivate any website when the WebCare has expired, and the client has not paid the renewal charge. We reserve the right to charge an administration fee of £100 plus VAT for reactivating WebCare.</li>
 	<li class="x_MsoNormal">If the client does not use Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. WebCare services, then the management and hosting of the domain name are the full responsibility of the client.</li>
 	<li class="x_MsoNormal">If the client does not wish to renew WebCare, or do not wish to have their site hosted with us after completion, the site files and associated data can be made available to the client for free on request and the domain name can be transferred to the client’s registrar account. Should the client instruct us to upload and configure the site and domain name to a third-party server this work will be subject to charge.</li>
 	<li class="x_MsoNormal">Elevate Online marketing Ltd. reserve the right to delete the website from our servers 3 months after the date your WebCare service expired if you choose to not renew WebCare.</li>
 	<li class="x_MsoNormal">Elevate Online marketing Ltd. offer free SSL with sites we host and manage DNS for. If you wish to manage DNS independently, we cannot provide support for SSL. SSL is provided for 1 year at no charge when you purchase a website and host the website with an Elevate Online marketing Ltd. WebCare package.</li>
 	<li class="x_MsoNormal">SSL is provided via letsencrypt.org. If letsencrypt.org are not able to provide an SSL certificate for any reason including technical failure, Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. will make recommendations for other SSL providers. This will be charged at the advertised cost by the SSL provider as well as a £50 installation fee. The client will have the option to proceed with this SSL certificate or not.</li>
 	<li class="x_MsoNormal">WebCare packages that include WebAssist afford the client up to 20 minutes of updates to the site per calendar month. Unused minutes / months cannot be rolled over. Updates are limited to text/image based changes on a per request basis. Requests for changes to site coding, updates to plugins, or changes that exceed the work included in WebAssist are subject to charge.</li>
 	<li class="x_MsoNormal">WebCare Packages that include WebShield afford the client cost free fixes in the event that the site has been compromised. ElevateOM monitor all sites and will attempt to identify and rectify issues as and when they happen. In some instances a vulnerability may not be picked up by our monitoring systems however fixes are still offered cost free when we are made aware.</li>
 	<li class="x_MsoNormal">Payments for WebCare products are non-refundable and non-transferable.</li>
 	<li class="x_MsoNormal">As part of all WebCare packages you receive DDoS protection. This is provided via a third party, Cloudflare Inc. Our DDoS protection is intended to provide an extra security layer to your website in the event of a DDoS attack against your website or services. If your services are interrupted or taken offline due to a DDoS attack Elevate Online marketing Ltd. will endeavour to restore these services ASAP. We cannot be held liable financially or otherwise for a DDoS attack.</li>
 	<li class="x_MsoNormal">Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. do not take any responsibility for a client’s website rank on search engines. This also includes any potential website downtime that can occur. When updating, changing, creating and hosting a client’s website, there could be a change in the websites search engine ranking.</li>
</ol>
<strong>Domain Names and Links</strong>
<ol>
 	<li>If required, a domain name will be registered by Elevate Online Marketing Ltd. on behalf of the client once we have received payment in full. Although the domain name is registered to Elevate Online marketing Ltd., the client is the legal owner of the domain and if they request to have details changed or the domain transferred elsewhere, we will do this within a reasonable timeframe.</li>
