<p>Cold selling can be an added expense, especially for businesses with modest budgets. If you want to get noticed, the biggest piece of advice is to act early.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center"} -->
<h2 class="has-text-align-center">Invest In Paid Search And Google Ads</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Paid advertising campaigns are an effective eCommerce marketing strategy you can use to attract more customers this Black Friday.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>According to a recent study, almost half of all Black Friday deals are now decided by paid search advertising.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>While organic traffic is the best way to rank high on Google and other search engine results pages&nbsp;(SERPs), paid ads can be a game-changer for Black Friday and Cyber Monday eCommerce marketing.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Running PPC <em>(Pay Per Click)</em> ads in the days leading up to Black Friday weekend is an excellent marketing tool for increasing online traffic.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2>Optimise your content and offers</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The same goes for the use of keywords in your content. By relying on tools like Google Keyword Planners and Google Trends you can find the keywords to use in the descriptions and content of your site to maximise both the quality and quantity of your traffic.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Content optimisation focuses on addressing issues in the following:</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li>Internal links</li><li>Keywords</li><li>Featured snippets</li><li>URLs</li><li>Readability</li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center"} -->
<h2 class="has-text-align-center">Send an E-Mail With Special Discounts</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Although&nbsp;emails&nbsp;are one of the oldest forms of digital marketing, they should still be seen as valid and effective allies. Equally, everyone loves a special offer!</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Sending your contact list an email promising them a special discount will increase the anticipation when Black Friday arrives and gives them a reason to go and explore your products on offer in the hope of bagging a great deal.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Don't make discounts impossible and torturous to understand, however. Try to keep it simple, and be direct and immediate with your wording.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Discover the best ideas and tips to </strong><a href="a"><strong>create a perfect newsletter</strong></a><strong> for Black Friday in our blog post</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center"} -->
<h2 class="has-text-align-center">Create a Black Friday landing page</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Creating a landing page within your eCommerce site, entirely dedicated to grouping Black Friday offers is a great way to maintain your positioning within the SERP (the Google search results page) and thus ensures that users can find your products more easily.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Creating&nbsp;specific content makes&nbsp;it easier for your audience to find you, especially those looking for offers. Make sure you create the page in advance of the big sale so that Googlebot has time to discover and index the page and its products.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center"} -->
<h2 class="has-text-align-center">Retrieve abandoned carts with a personalised message and “one-time “offers</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Sales naturally fall through the cracks, and a high cart abandonment rate is quite common for online retailers during Black Friday events. Optimising and recovering abandoned carts&nbsp;is and must for any eCommerce business not just during seasonal periods but as a normal part of your marketing strategy.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Creating a customer remarketing campaign can increase the chances of getting customers back to your site and completing the sales journey. Retargeting your visitors with a paid ad campaign allows you to bring them back to your store and back to the point of sale.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->"


