"<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Search engine optimisation (SEO) is one of, if not, the most important internet marketing methods for growing your online business. It not only supports search engine algorithms in accurately indexing web pages but also enhances user experience. SEO can also greatly increase organic traffic and continuously improve your site's rating in the SERP (Search Engine Results Pages).</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>However, If you’re just not getting the traction you need or you’ve noticed a sudden decline in rankings and visitors then some, or all of the below SEO mistakes could be to blame.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Let's look at 5 common mistakes you can address right now to improve website SEO.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Poor Titles And Descriptions</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Pay close attention to your title and description tags, especially on your home page or high traffic pages.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Your description (which usually appears as the snippet below the link to your site in search results) should entice people to click on your results, letting searchers know that the site provides an answer to their query or is a good resource. If not, you may want to optimise the meta description and experiment with them on high traffic pages to see what the best result is.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Keyword Stuffing</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>When you stuff your content with keywords; by stuffing, we mean high volume stuffing; you risk not just being perceived as spam by your readers, but you also risk getting penalised by Google.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Keyword stuffing comes in a variety of shapes and sizes, but it usually involves repeating a phrase or term (often robotically) in your content over and over to rank better on Google – this doesn’t work and Google upped its game a long time ago to combat this practice. We strongly advise against this.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>The importance of link building</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The proper usage of backlinks and link building efforts allows a company’s website to be optimised and move up the SERP. External links boost the authority of a website and are rewarded by Google. When this element is overlooked, you run the risk of your position dropping over time.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The presence of links within your content (backlinks) allows the site to be organised and structured hierarchically, improving both the end user's and search engine's navigability.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>On the subject of links; broken links on your website can also contribute to problems, theynot only affect the user experience but also make it more difficult for search engines to index your site. When it comes to increasing website traffic and rankings, locating and fixingbroken links on your website is crucial.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Slow website speed</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>One of the most common SEO mistakes that leads to a high bounce rate is slow website speed. No one in today's fast-paced world wants to wait for a website to load. This means that if your website's loading time is too slow, it may be affecting its performance.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Google is clear that page speed is a ranking factor for searches performed on websites and mobile devices</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Checking your website's speed can assist you in figuring out why it's so slow. Various free online tools will also give you advice on how to properly tackle these issues in lowering your bounce rate and clawing back your rankings.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Poor content or copying content</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>This may sound obvious, but if you're copying content from other sources then it’s most likely that Google isn't going to place you anywhere near the top of page rankings. Google is smart; and utilises automatic systems to score websites based on a range of characteristics, one of which is detecting copied content.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Equally, you’re not going to improve your organic SEO this way, and if the plagiarism is substantial, you may be reported to Google's DMC. Not the best way to approach SEO!Creating new content and updating existing articles is a good way to build upon and improve your SEO.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Have trouble with your Google ranking?</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><a href="https://www.elevateom.com/seo/">ElevateOM SEO</a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>ElevateOM are digital marketing experts and SEO consultants. We use highly accurate tools to analyse and report our findings and constantly monitor your website’s search engine performance to ensure maximum results.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><a href="https://www.elevateom.com/contact/">Contact</a> us to discuss a complete SEO campaign strategy to increase your visibility, enquiries &amp; sales!</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->"





"<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>All online businesses, especially small to medium-sized ones, can benefit from a welcome boost in advertising with PPC (Pay Per Click) marketing campaigns.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>A successful PPC marketing campaign can yield greater interactions and profits in a shorter time than many other online or local marketing campaigns. It is the ideal method for fast, quality traffic and conversions.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":4} -->
<h4 class="has-text-align-center">PPC Advertising - The Basics&nbsp;&nbsp;</h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Pay-Per-Click (PPC) is a marketing channel where you, the advertiser, pays a certain amountevery time one of your promotional ads is clicked. Effectively, it's a way of buying visits to your site, rather than obtaining them organically via SEO or content marketing, which when combined, can serve as a great, all-encompassing digital marketing strategy. In time, PPC campaigns will make a great contribution to the growth of your online business.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Let's take a look at a few main advantages of this form of digital advertising.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":4} -->
<h4 class="has-text-align-center">Reach The Right Audience</h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>During a PPC campaign, you can choose exactly when and where your ads will appear based on a range of parameters such as location, website, keywords, time, data, device and many others.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>You can then show your business ads to a very specific and engaged audience, increasing the quality of traffic on your website. This kind of adaptability allows you to segment your market and reach the proper demographic, giving you the visibility you need.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":4} -->
<h4 class="has-text-align-center">More Immediate results</h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>PPC advertising is the fastest way to create a promotional campaign and achieve results in a short period of time. If you have an existing business website, all you need to do is create ads and run them on the best platforms to increase website traffic.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>This is very different from an SEO campaign, which often requires a lot of time and attention to get the same type of positioning and traffic offered by Google Ads in the short term.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":4} -->
<h4 class="has-text-align-center">Gives You Total Control</h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>PPC also gives you added control of your over your campaign clearly and measurably; you can measure virtually everything related to your PPC campaign, including revenues, costs, clicks, views, visits, and more.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>As highlighted previously, thanks to this form of advertising, you pay only when a user clicks on your ad, visits your website or landing page. You'll know <em>exactly</em> how much you're spending from the minute you start your PPC campaign. Statistics and data are easily accessible, displaying the success of your campaigns, the sort of traffic they are driving, and the results they are producing in comparison to the initial budget.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":4} -->
<h4 class="has-text-align-center">Useful Data And Audience Insights</h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The data and information provided on Google Ads have significance that extends well beyond the performance of a PPC campaign. Each keyword's impression, click, and conversion data can be used to further improve upon existing SEO and content marketing strategies.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":4} -->
<h4 class="has-text-align-center">Geographic Relevance</h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Finally, pay-per-click is an excellent method for audience segmentation. It allows businesses to concentrate their efforts on a certain geographic location; i.e. local PPC campaigns. Many businesses who operate in a small geographic area find that advertising across the country is a waste of money and resources; instead, it would be much better to be able to have their ads displayed <strong><em>only</em></strong> to users in a specific area of operation.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":3} -->
<h3 class="has-text-align-center">Need help?</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:heading {"textAlign":"center","level":4} -->
<h4 class="has-text-align-center">Get PPC management &amp; Maximise Your Revenue with ElevateOM</h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>If you've recently begun a PPC advertising campaign but are having trouble managing it or thinking about embarking on a new campaign, <a href="https://www.elevateom.com/ppc/">Elevate OM’s PPC Services</a> can assist you in building a new campaign or optimising your existing one.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>We’re Certified Google Partners - that means we’re recognised for our expertise and experience in managing Google Adwords, giving you the best possible advice when it comes to marketing your business online.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><a href="https://www.elevateom.com/contact/">Contact Us</a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->"
"<!-- wp:heading {"level":4} -->
<h4><em>THE ART OF BEING A SOCIAL (MEDIA) BUTTERFLY</em></h4>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>From big brands to start-ups, every business at some point will embark on a social media campaign, no matter how big or small. And, It's impossible to have a digital strategy without mentioning “social networks”- from Facebook to Instagram, Twitter to YouTube, one thing is for sure; get it right and there is boundless potential to connect with huge audiences and reap great rewards.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>But…yes, but! There are certain things to bear in mind when dabbling in the social realm and, more importantly, a few things <em>to do</em> and <em>not to do </em>to be successful. Let’s take a look at a few to get you started.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->
<h5>Be Active!</h5>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Be lively and present on your socials to help give your digital reputation a boost. Start conversations with your followers, ask them what they think about a product, help them solve a product issue or simply provide free advice. All this will connect you to the people you want to be connected to while also gaining great insight into what people like about your products and services. However, when engaging with your followers, you also need to be prepared to handle negative feedback as well.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->
<h5>Show Your Strengths</h5>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Emphasise your company's distinct features and benefits. Be proud of your product or the level of service you provide. This will show current and new clients how proud you are of your company and, more importantly, how beneficial it would be for them to add you to their network.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->
<h5>Analyse your social media data</h5>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>If you don't keep track of your social media analytics, how will you know what's working and what isn’t? You should check your analytics at least once a week to make sure you are on track to beat your previous month/year’s performance or find new ways to increase poor performance.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->
<h5>Check out what your competitors are up to</h5>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Seeing what your competitors do allows you to compare your social media strategy with theirs. Think of it as free advice - If they are performing better than you in terms of engagement, you can change your strategy and make it more effective. Likewise, if your competitor is doing badly, you can understand what <em>not to do</em> to fall into the same trap.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":5} -->
<h5>Don’t be boring!</h5>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Yes. Don’t be boring; perhaps this is a bit of tough love, perhaps it’s obvious. One thing is for sure, it’s all too easy to become static and monotonous over time on social media. The first rule is to be daring and creative; experiment, play with ideas, study your audience, find out what they like best and what they don't, don't insist on the same type of content if it only ever gets the same few likes. Win the hearts of new users and build loyalty in your community by changing things often.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Don’t recycle post across the same socials</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Not all content is suitable for all social networks. A post that is successful on one may not experience the same on Facebook or Instagram, for example. Adapt your tone of voice and hone your strategy to achieve the best across all your channels.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3>Ready to venture out into the world of social media marketing?&nbsp;</h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Social Media Management with ElevateOM</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Would you like to learn more about how to integrate social networks into your digital communication? Our <a href="https://www.elevateom.com/social-media/">Social Media Team</a> will apply research to your business and competitors and create a plan of action and social media strategy to build your growing social presence.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><a href="https://www.elevateom.com/contact/">Contact Us</a></p>
