<p>These days, anyone can create a website, but only a few can boast a truly effective website. What does an&nbsp;<em>“effective website"</em>&nbsp;mean and what are the characteristics that distinguish it from an&nbsp;<em>"ineffective"</em>&nbsp;one?&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>In this article, we will try to provide you with some simple, but useful information which you can use to benchmark whether your site is effective and if it is not, how to address certain issues.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2>Go for clean graphics</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Simplicity, minimalism, linearity are the key concepts that dominate web design trends. Many sites tend to favour content over images, but the importance of using quality photos should be emphasised.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Colours and photos must be well balanced, clear and incisive. The use of poor-quality graphics and content will cause users to never return to your website. It is therefore, absolutely necessary to show high quality images to influence a potential customer's purchase decision and improve the overall quality of your ecommerce site.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Remember that images make a huge difference!</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2>Clarity</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>When the user doesn't know what to expect after clicking on a link or doesn't know where to click to find the information they are looking for, it will cause in them to leave your site. So, make sure you create a website that is easy for users to navigate and understand.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The use of clear and intuitive categories and labels serves to communicate what your business is dedicated to. From the first moment, users will know they are in the right place and how to find the information they are looking for. Pay particular attention to the phrases and language you use to communicate with users, in order to facilitate their search.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2><strong>Search Engine Optimisation</strong></h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Your goal, when you decide to create an effective website, is to translate your&nbsp;<em>potential</em>&nbsp;leads into customers, and to sell, you need to attract a lot of people to your site.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>This won’t be possible if you do not carry out good SEO practice, allowing you to improve visibility of the website rankings on search engines. The higher you are positioned within these engines, the greater your chances of getting noticed in the crowd.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>For more, read our blog about&nbsp;<a href="https://elevateom.com/why-seo-is-vital-to-your-sme/">Why SEO is Important</a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2>Write useful content for your users</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Website content writing</strong>&nbsp;must be of quality, original and relevant.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>There is nothing worse than boring, uninteresting, soulless&nbsp;<strong>web content</strong>, so, avoid copying and pasting from the corporate brochure.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Always ask yourself what your users want and think about what they might find interesting. Answering their questions with relevant and clear answers is your goal. If your responses are appreciated, people will be happy to share your content on their social channels.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Read our blog on&nbsp;<a href="https://elevateom.com/want-to-write-better-social-content/"><strong>how to write better content</strong></a></p>
