<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2>Call to Action</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>CTA marketing</strong>&nbsp;is one of the most important points: whether it is the "buy", "subscribe" or "contact us" button, it must be positioned wisely, because it is the&nbsp;<strong>call to action on a website&nbsp;</strong>that actually converts a visitor into a lead.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>A CTA allows the user to enter an area that you have designated for them; a landing page, an information page or a page to fill in the data for a contact request.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>From your point of view, calls to action are really important, because they allow you to guide the visitor in the direction you want and to offer content made especially for them. The CTA must also stand out visually and stand out from the rest of the page, perhaps with a different colour or a particular font.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>We hope that these tips will provide you with a starting point towards tackling the design and effectiveness of your website and guiding you towards a more modern, more successful and professional online business.</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->"
"<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Instagram is a fundamental resource for reaching and creating relationships with your audience. However, there are some rules to follow to make the most of this social network and obtain tangible benefits.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Need a strategy to get your Instagram profile off the ground, or want to know how to increase Instagram followers? Follow these Instagram marketing tips steps and you’ll be on the right path!&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>1. Determine Who Your Audience is&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Let's start with the basics. First of all, the first two questions you need to ask yourself are:&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>·</strong> Who are you trying to reach with your Instagram profile?&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>· Are you sure your audience is using the app?&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>It's smart to plan your Instagram campaigns with a clearly defined audience in mind&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Researching your demographic is essential before you start posting Instagram content. Define the age, gender, interests of your ideal audience so you can properly cater to the content.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>2. Define Your Goals&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>What are your goals? What do you want to do with your Instagram profile?&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>When you create an Instagram marketing strategy, it's essential to always have in mind what goals you want to achieve. I recommend that you make a proper list of the goals you intend to achieve. For example:&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>· Collaborate with companies</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>· Increase followers&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>· Sell your followers</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>· Engage with Instagram users&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>3. Create a Content Strategy&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Potentially the most decisive part of your marketing strategy is deciding what to post to enhance and improve your Instagram profile and achieve your goals.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>First, you need to understand which of the following content formats is best suited to your users:&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>· Photo&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>· Video&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>·</strong> User-Generated Content&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>· Stories&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>All the while making sure your Instagram feed has the quality and aesthetically pleasing photos and videos!&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Understanding what to post on Instagram and choosing the right content and format will help increase Instagram engagement and appear on your followers feed, allowing you to get more likes and views.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>5. Create a Content Calendar</strong>&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>To avoid posting at the last minute in a hurry I suggest you make a calendar that will allow you to organise and plan your feed.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Being consistent and systematic is more important than how often to post on Instagram. Instagram's algorithm favours an account that posts twice a day.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The best tactic for choosing how regularly to post is to observe when your followers are most active throughout the week.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>6. Plan and Schedule the Captions&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Another important factor influencing your strategy is the need to have good Instagram captions! This is where you talk to your audience and get the chance to talk about yourself or your brand.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Remember to always use language that is in line with your audience, use language that is easy to understand, don’t opt for big words or complex and long-winded phrases or sentences.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The hashtags are just as important for Instagram and must be placed directly in your caption or the first comment.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>During the process of analysing your target audience and competitors, you will have an idea of the most used hashtags in your industry, but it is always worth doing further research.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>7. Monitor Progress&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>This is the last step. Use Instagram Insights to get a basic idea of what's effective or not with your audience. You will understand if your Instagram organic growth strategy is doing well or not. If it's not going the way you thought, try to understand why and fix it.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Conclusions&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>In this article, we explained a few steps to building an effective organic growth strategy on Instagram. Take your time and experiment – you’ll soon find what works and what doesn’t.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>If you’d like to know more or have a discussion about paid ads on Instagram for your clients, get in touch with one of our digital marketing experts at <a href="https://elevateom.com/contact/">https://elevateom.com/contact/</a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->"
"<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>2021 is in its infancy still, but 2020 has given us an important lesson to all those who did not believe that the internet could get bigger and busier in such a short space of time: the future of sales is firmly online and those who cannot seize the opportunities that digital has to offer, will soon find themselves totally cut off from the market.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The situation generated by the Covid-19 pandemic has forced people to spend much more time at home and therefore today more than ever consumers are looking for information online instead of physically going to the store, and more and more often, they will purchase directly online.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>What should companies expect to implement in their strategies for 2021?&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Below we’ll share with you a few tips and ideas that should feature in your digital marketing plan, and remain firmly in place going forward.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Social Commerce&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Even those who have never heard of it before will be able to easily guess what we mean when we talk about “<strong>social commerce</strong>”: it is the sale of products made directly through social networks, often taking advantage of posts or comments.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The vast majority of online shopping usually happens like this:&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>· the potential buyer researches the product that interests him/her&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>· looks for useful information on the product and the brand (also through social networks)&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>· when he/she decides to make the purchase, the sale takes place on the brand's <strong>e-commerce site&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>So why not simplify this long process by moving sales directly to social media? <strong>With social commerce</strong>, the entire purchasing process, including the sale of the product, takes place directly on social networks.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Social Media Marketing&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Social media marketing</strong> often appears as something boring and ineffective, but the reality is it requires you to be present with a certain continuity on the social networks where your ideal target customer is present and active.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Facebook has become a powerful tool for even small businesses and can <strong>increase web traffic</strong> and profits when used effectively.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Facebook uses very sophisticated audience targeting features that can filter your audience based on a variety of factors, including age, gender, social location, previous purchase activity or expression of interest.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>By using these targeting techniques, Facebook ads increase the likelihood that your ad will be relevant to the people you want to see it.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Facebook also helps determine the goal of your ads and you can then choose the type of focus you want for your ads. You can also choose ad placement based on the experience you want your potential buyer to have.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Search Engine Optimisation&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Once your 2021 strategy and marketing plan has been defined, in addition to <strong>email marketing</strong>, <strong>SEO</strong> is always the next step.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Search engine optimisation</strong> is the process of "formatting" your web content to make it more easily intercepted by search engines. This increases the likelihood of your content appearing when your target prospect searches for topics, answers, information, products, services, and small businesses like yours.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>SEO is extremely important for small businesses because being able to <strong>optimise your web content</strong> to bring them to the top of the <strong>search engine rankings </strong>always means having a possible competitive advantage over your competitors.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Also, aim to properly set up your <strong>Google My Business</strong> profile. Make sure you complete all fields, including bio, product and service descriptions, opening hours, etc.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>You should also share the review link on Google and encourage your satisfied customers to leave their feedback. Their feedback affects your credibility, and Google will also reward you by improving your position in its rankings.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Voice Search in 2021&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>A second trend to take into consideration during this new year is that linked to <strong>voice search</strong>: more and more often potential customers use their <strong>voice to search</strong> on the internet; complicit in this new trend is the increasingly widespread diffusion of virtual assistants&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>(such as Alexa, Siri, Bixby and Google Assistant).&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The content we offer on the web must be optimised for this type of search, for example by exploiting the <strong>long-tail keywords</strong>. The SEO specialist of our company will have to take into account the fact that, when users use voice research, they resort to longer and more complex sentences, ask questions, in short, they use a more natural and spoken language.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Conclusion</strong>&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>To ensure success, a company must keep customer touchpoints under their control. Make sure these basic tips are part of your 2021 marketing plan so your brand will experience a new period of engagement and profitability.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>If you’d like to know more or have a discussion about improving your <strong>digital marketing strategy</strong> in 2021, get in touch with one of our digital marketing experts at <a href="https://elevateom.com/contact/">https://elevateom.com/contact/</a></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->"


















