<p>In this short article, we'll give you some interesting insights into why they are so important for the growth of your business and how to ask for reviews.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Why use customer reviews to grow your business?&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Having satisfied customers is too precious a resource not to exploit it and consequently increase the growth and success of any business!&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>But why are online reviews so important for getting new customers? It is very simple to explain:&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Building Trust&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>When a product or service is recommended by one or more people who have actually tried it, potential customers feel calmer and are more likely to buy it.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Positive reviews that highlight the qualities of your work have a major impact on your professional image. A potential customer reading positive reviews about you will feel more comfortable trusting you.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Increase Conversion Rate&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Not all users who visit your website are ready to buy right away. They often need to figure out if what you are offering is really right for them. This is why the strategic use of a review can make a significant contribution to pushing the consumer to choose you.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Customer Insights&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>By listening to the opinion of those who use your services, you can collect interesting ideas to improve your work and demonstrate that you are a serious company or professional who knows how to listen to their customers and wants to improve.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Improve SEO&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>They improve SEO if you get positive reviews on different platforms, the SEO of your site will benefit a lot and more customers will be able to find you easily on the internet. It is important to remember to insert the website link in the profile (for example on the Facebook page or Google My Business).&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Tips for increasing your customer reviews&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>As we've seen, positive reviews are a lifesaver for your business. Let’s have a look at some of the best ways to increase your customer reviews.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Design a custom template&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>One of the best ways you can start getting positive reviews is to be able to contact old customers who have used your company and it must be written in a way that is clear, direct and easily understandable. During the drafting of the email, customers should be treated in a subjective and personal way. It may be useful to add some details that relate to the relationship between the customer and the company in question yet still appeal to a wide number of people – you don’t want to write individual emails!&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Ask to leave a review at the end of their journey&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Asking for a review at the end of the customer journey is certainly a great way to collect the so-called "hot opinions". Being a time when customers' enthusiasm is at its peak, it will be easier for them to leave positive reviews. These include a link within them that can be used to direct customers to the place where you want to receive reviews. This function will be used by people to be able to express an opinion about their experience discreetly.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Offer customers something in exchange&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
