"<!-- wp:heading {"level":3} -->
<h3><em>5 TIPS to improve your Local SEO</em></h3>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Mastering&nbsp;<strong>how to get on the first page of Google</strong>&nbsp;is the ultimate goal for most companies. But more important than ranking first overall, is to appear first,&nbsp;<em>locally</em>. That is why Local SEO and Google's Local algorithm are increasingly important and ways to improve local SEO should be your main focus.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Local SEO is very important to bear in mind for companies, especially for those that operate within a strong territory or competition. Having good Local SEO positioning on Google allows your company to appear visible, possibly in the first pages, to every user who carries out a localised search.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Here are some useful tips to improve the local ranking of your site.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":1} -->
<h1>1. Start with your&nbsp;<strong>Google My Business page</strong></h1>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Google My Business service was created by Google Plus in 2014. This platform allows a professional or company to create a profile with all the details of their business. This data will then be inserted into Google Maps.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>For those who are just beginning, the advice is to fill in all the descriptive fields trying to use the right keywords, obviously making sure that the description is written for human beings and therefore genuine.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>What data can be entered? The possibilities are many and to have a detailed and useful profile for Local SEO it is good to specify:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li>Description of the activity</li><li>Commercial category to which you belong</li><li>Pictures related to the activity</li><li>Opening/closing times</li><li>Address</li><li>Telephone number</li><li>Mail</li><li>Reviews of users</li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>In all probability, you may have neglected this area of local SEO optimisation - from the lack of contact information to the inclusion in the wrong categories which alienate the really interested leads. Fortunately, this is all easily fixed and learning how to create Google My Business page is easy.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":1} -->
<h1>2. Use other&nbsp;<strong>online directories</strong>&nbsp;on the web&nbsp;</h1>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>These are portals and platforms where you can enter the URL of your and information about your business for free. Users very often rely on these as business directories, because they are considered safe and free.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Some popular directories are:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li>Apple Maps</li><li>Yellow Pages</li><li>Foursquare</li><li>Yahoo's Localworks&nbsp;</li><li>Google Places</li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Being featured in these directories can have a big impact on your ranking. In addition to directories, it is useful to have good reviews on other sites such as:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li>Yelp</li><li>Glassdoor</li><li>TripAdvisor</li><li>Hot Frog</li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>These are very popular sites, where people can leave comments and reviews about different types of local businesses. Keep in mind that one of the most important factors in ranking your business is positive reviews.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>In fact, according to Google, high-quality reviews can significantly improve your online visibility.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":1} -->
<h1>3. NAP</h1>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Not the sleeping “NAP” you’re thinking about - NAP (name and place) refers to information about your business.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>When filling out your forms, you must always check that you have entered consistent information in all the lists in which you are present on the web.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Google cares about its credibility and it is vital that the information is accurate.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Your name, address, and phone number must match on all profiles to make it easier for customers to connect with your business.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":1} -->
<h1>4. Keyword research for Local SEO&nbsp;</h1>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Research your company’s keywords- but,&nbsp;<strong><em>what keywords should you use? How many keywords should you use</em></strong><em>?</em></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Don’t worry! Google Keyword Planner can help you</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list -->
<ul><li>Enter keywords that are relevant to your business and that will be found by local users</li><li>Monitor the search volume of your keywords</li><li>Monitor the degree of difficulty and relevance of keywords.</li></ul>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Implementing this type of research and keeping it active over time allows companies to always be ready to respond to hypothetical requests from users.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading {"level":1} -->
<h1>5. Generate fresh content</h1>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Search engines favour sites that offer frequent updates in their content. This means that if your site stays the same for months, it won't get good results from a positioning point of view.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The best way to always have new content is to&nbsp;<strong>learn how to create a blog</strong>&nbsp;and constantly insert new content. This blog should be on the company website and not in a separate site.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Using the keywords, you’ve researched about your company, now would be a good time to begin using them by entering the necessary keywords according to the rules of&nbsp;<a href="https://elevateom.com/how-to-create-the-perfect-blog-content-that-converts-into-sales/">SEO copywriting</a>.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Want to know&nbsp;<strong>how to write better content for social media</strong>? Read our&nbsp;<a href="https://elevateom.com/want-to-write-better-social-content/">featured blog</a>&nbsp;on the subject.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Here are just some of the main elements you need to understand what Local SEO is and&nbsp;why Google's Local algorithm is so important today.&nbsp;So,&nbsp;don’t delay, begin optimising your Local SEO today!</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->"
"<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>Increasing organic website traffic is not an easy thing to accomplish but it’s is not impossible - by investing a bit of time and commitment, and a few successful strategies, you’ll generate more traffic in no time.&nbsp;</strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Let’s take a look at 3 ways we can do this and understand why it’s important to work hard on these aspects and improve them:&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"fontSize":"medium"} -->
<p class="has-medium-font-size">Gain valuable links to your content&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>1. Use internal links – Internal links help Google understand the context and relationships between the different articles on your website. It then uses this information as classification signals.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Once you have accumulated a decent amount of content for SEO, you can cite it on your blog and your website, guiding visitors to more relevant content marketing. This can keep visitors on your website longer, which helps improve search engine rankings. However, don't abuse internal links - using too many of them could make your content look like spam.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>We recommend that you make a habit of linking to your older articles in your new articles.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>2. Search for keywords - SEO tools are essential for identifying various parameters related to your site. Backlinks, competitors, keywords etc. They can be collected by these tools and this information is useful for classifying your website and, ultimately, for positioning the site on Google.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>3. Find Influencers - There are several ways to find influencers in your sector. Google gives you access to a large online database. Plus, you can find the right influencer for your niche on Youtube, an ideal platform for influencer marketing.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Another tool you can use to search for influencers is a link analysis tool. By checking the *backlinks of your competitors, you can understand where the traffic is coming from and find influencers in your sector.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>*A backlink is an inbound link to your content from an external website. Backlinks are one of the most influential signals in Google rankings.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"fontSize":"medium"} -->
<p class="has-medium-font-size">Keep your content fresh&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Is your website full of old content that has stopped attracting visitors? If so, you may be able to revitalise this content by updating it for the current year!&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>SEO is constantly evolving and if your site only has old content, you won't attract results. The following changes can boost a page's search ranking quickly:&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>· Update of the year in the page title, for example, change from “hottest trends of 2019” to “hottest trends of 2020”&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>· Correction of any broken links in the content&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>· Updating outdated screenshots&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>· Using statistics for the current year&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>· Correction of broken images&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>· Make sure your content stays up to date. It doesn't take long and can make a big difference to your site!&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"fontSize":"medium"} -->
<p class="has-medium-font-size">Indexed Pages&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The most common mistake is to confuse "indexing" with "ranking".&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The are two related but completely different things!&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>By indexing on search engines, we mean “making a website or blog visible among the results that a search engine returns (regardless of position)”.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>By positioning, on the other hand, we mean " all those techniques aimed at making a website in the best possible position among the results for certain keywords ".&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Indexing is the basis (without that you can't rank anything), ranking comes next and is about the ability to get your site or page up among the top positions on Google or other search engines. Pages must be indexed on Google correctly, using the Google Webmaster Tool.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
