<!-- wp:paragraph {"fontSize":"large"} -->
<p class="has-large-font-size">The Importance of Usability&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>We all&nbsp;know the feeling of frustration when you want to access a site and it is slow to load&nbsp;-&nbsp;As a user,&nbsp;it will have happened to you countless times and you will be familiar with the instinct to leave the website immediately.&nbsp;In addition to the content, a winning website must be developed&nbsp;towards those who&nbsp;will use it; in other words, it must be able to combine an attractive and recognisable design with&nbsp;good&nbsp;usability for the target audience.&nbsp;Only then will your website be&nbsp;successful,&nbsp;and&nbsp;your audience&nbsp;will be able to get the most out of it.&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p><strong>You can ask  yourself a few  questions that will help you understand where you need to make usability improvements: </strong></p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:list {"ordered":true} -->
<ol><li>How is the page loading speed?&nbsp;</li></ol>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:list {"ordered":true,"start":2} -->
<ol start="2"><li>Are the texts understandable and do they communicate the message promptly?&nbsp;</li></ol>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:list {"ordered":true,"start":3} -->
<ol start="3"><li>Are the calls to action clear and visible?&nbsp;</li></ol>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:list {"ordered":true,"start":4} -->
<ol start="4"><li>Is the menu well structured?&nbsp;</li></ol>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:list {"ordered":true,"start":5} -->
<ol start="5"><li>Is the user's path hindered or does it run smoothly to purchase?&nbsp;</li></ol>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:list {"ordered":true,"start":6} -->
<ol start="6"><li>Are there any errors or other slowdowns?&nbsp;</li></ol>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:list {"ordered":true,"start":7} -->
<ol start="7"><li>Are the pages mobile friendly?&nbsp;</li></ol>
<!-- /wp:list -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>&nbsp;<br>It’s&nbsp;crucial to make sure that your site does not present these problems, considering the limited time available to the&nbsp;visitor and the difficulty in capturing their attention.&nbsp;<br>Furthermore, if your site is too slow, it will be penalised by Google in&nbsp;page&nbsp;rankings, as speed is one of the fundamental factors for correct indexing. &nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph {"fontSize":"large"} -->
<p class="has-large-font-size">Keep your website updated&nbsp;</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>From&nbsp;the&nbsp;images of the products&nbsp;you sell&nbsp;to the graphics of the site itself, everything must be up-to-date and pleasant, with professional care. Would you go shopping at a store whose owner&nbsp;doesn't&nbsp;bother fixing the broken window?&nbsp;Perhaps not.&nbsp;The same goes for&nbsp;your website.&nbsp;Your&nbsp;website is&nbsp;a&nbsp;showcase&nbsp;of the products and/or services&nbsp;you’re&nbsp;offering, take care of it and keep it updated&nbsp;and you’ll have visitors returning.&nbsp;</p>
